HEADWORD: Buccinum
<hw>Buc"ci*num</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
trumpet, a trumpet shell.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
large univalve mollusks abundant in the arctic seas. It includes the
common whelk (<spn>Buccinum undatum</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

